text:
Reposting <https://HubSpotdev.slack.com/archives/CFPRTEGTX/p1624460927141200|this> here as this is more of an idea.

It's really nice that it's possible to reuse repeating patterns like buttons using macros. This way you can create a `renderButton(arg)` macro and use it in other modules. But in this case you have to copy/paste the required fields to all the modules you want to use `renderButton` macro in. Is there a way to avoid this copy pasting? If there was a way to define `fields.json` as `fields.js` as a JS module, then we could just import the file and merge it to the `fields.js` of the module we want to add those fields.

Example:

```// Maybe use JS modules

const buttonFields = require("./buttonFields.js");

module.exports = [
 {
    label: "Some label",
    name: "some_name"
 },
  ...buttonFields, 
];```
